tool_description: Odds data API for NFL, NBA, MLB, EPL, AFL and loads more, from US, UK, EU and Aussie bookmakers. Get started for free!
name: Live Sports Odds
title: Live Sports Odds

api_list.name: /v4/sports/{sport}/odds
api_list.description: Returns list of live and upcoming games for a given sport, showing bookmaker odds for the specified region and markets. Set the `sport` to a `sport_key` from the /sports endpoint. Alternatively if `sport=upcoming`, it will return a list of the next 8 upcoming games across all sports, as well as any live games. For more info, see [list of available sports](https://the-odds-api.com/sports-odds-data/sports-apis.html) and [list of available bookmakers](https://the-odds-api.com/sports-odds-data/bookmaker-apis.html).

required_parameters.name: sport
required_parameters.description: sport key for which to return games and odds

required_parameters.name: regions
required_parameters.description: Determines which bookmakers appear in the response. Can be a comma delimited list of regions. Each region will count as 1 request against the usage quota for each market. Most use cases will only need to specify one region. For a list of bookmakers by region, see https://the-odds-api.com/sports-odds-data/bookmaker-apis.html

optional_parameters.name: markets
optional_parameters.description: The odds market to return. Can be a comma delimited list of odds markets. Defaults to h2h (head to head / moneyline). Outrights only avaialable for select sports. Note each market counts as 1 request against the usage quota.

optional_parameters.name: dateFormat
optional_parameters.description: Format of returned timestamps. Can be iso (ISO8601) or unix timestamp (seconds since epoch)

api_list.name: /v4/sports/{sport}/scores
api_list.description: Returns list of live and upcoming games for a given sport, and optionally recently completed games. Live and completed games will contain scores. **Currently in beta** and only available for selected sports. For more info, see the [list of available sports](https://the-odds-api.com/sports-odds-data/sports-apis.html)

required_parameters.name: sport
required_parameters.description: sport key for which to return games and odds

optional_parameters.name: daysFrom
optional_parameters.description: The number of days in the past from which to return completed games. Valid values are integers from `1` to `3`. If this field is missing, only live and upcoming games are returned.

schema.description: A list of live, upcoming and optionally recently completed games

id.description: A unique 32 character identifier for the event.

sport_key.description: A unique slug for the sport. Use this as the "sport" param in the /odds and /scores requests

sport_title.description: A presentable title of the sport. Occassionally this value can change, for example if a league undergoes a name change or change in sponsorship.

commence_time.description: The match start time (ISO 8601 formatted). This will be unix timestamp integer if the dateFormat query param is set to dateFormat=unix.

completed.description: true if the game has finished, otherwise false

home_team.description: The home team. If home/away is not applicable for the sport (such as MMA and Tennis), it will be one of the participants. Null for outrights (futures) events.

away_team.description: The away team. If home/away is not applicable for the sport (such as MMA and Tennis), it will be one of the participants. Null for outrights (futures) events.

scores.description: A list of teams and their scores. List will be empty if game has not started.

score.description: The most recent score for the participant

last_update.description: ISO8601 datetime of when the scores were last updated. Will be null if game has not started

api_list.name: /v4/sports
api_list.description: Returns a list of available sports and tournaments. Use the `sports_key` in requests for /odds and /scores endpoints.

optional_parameters.name: all
optional_parameters.description: When excluded, only recently updated (in-season) sports appear. Include this paramter to see all available sports
